    {
      "id": "1b64750c-f3ba-80f1-a175-de0f8793976e",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Analysis of logs requires the transformation of the time-series-esque set of data into meaningful SRL constructs. The authors explore a different way of mapping interactions to SRL construct: Trace Parsing Methodology. They attempt to use 4 different forms of trace parsing and conclude that the choice of parsing method clearly affects process identification and sequencing. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
